2. Ecastercide.

The Christian Easter was preceded by a fast and followed by seven weeks of rejoicing. Thus defined, Lent and Eastertide may claim attestation of their observance from extreme antiquity. For the fast before the festival, it will suffice to cite in a general way the documents relating to the paschal controversy at the end of the second century.
